#!N  #!Rtall15 Controlling the 
Viewing Direction #!N #!N #!N To change the viewing direction, select 
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Set View #!EF in the dialog box (see  #!Lvcbox6,dxall15 f Figure 6  #!EL  ). 
The list of choices that appears includes 7 directional views of 
the object (Top, Bottom, etc.). Because these "head on" views show 
only "one side" of an object (tending to flatten its appearance), 
the list also offers 7 corresponding "off" views (Off Top, Off 
Bottom, etc.). #!Cbrown #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*    #!Rvcbox6 #!N Graphics omitted from Online 
Documentation. Please see the manual. #!N #!N Figure 6. View Control 
Dialog Box. This dialog box is activated from the Options pull-down 
menu of the Image window (see  #!Limwin5,dxall9 f Figure 5  #!EL  ). #!EF #!N #!EC 
#!N #!N When you select a view of an object, the 
image is automatically altered (note the highlighted  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Execute #!EF in 
the menu bar). #!N #!N #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   Next Topic #!EF #!N 
